Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses achievable rates of NFDM and WDM, which is a topic related to information theory. 
2. cs.OH (Optimization and Control): The paper may involve optimization of the transmission system to achieve higher rates. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper may discuss the application of NFDM and WDM in networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper is related to communication and networking as it discusses the performance of different multiplexing techniques. 
5. cs.PHYS (Physics and Society): The paper may involve the study of physical phenomena in the transmission of signals through fiber optics.
